						<summary>

						<p>Same wall.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Kaṉṉaradēva (Kṛishṇa III): Year 24 = 962-63 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription records a gift by a certain Tirunāvukkaraiśi of one gong and three trumpets towards which he gave a sum of 5 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of <hi rend="italic">poṉ</hi> to the temple of the god Tiruppulippagavar of Śiṟṟiṅgūr, a <hi rend="italic">brahmadēyam.</hi> It is stated that the temple managers <hi rend="italic">(kōyiluḍaiyār)</hi> received the gift and agreed to provide the above-mentioned articles to the temple.</p>						

						</summary>
